// @emit-error ref-list field element type is not interned
// Floor: a struct-element ARRAY whose element struct carries a NULLABLE-LIST field
// (`{a: {z: f64[] | null}[]}`). Such an element struct is an unsupported array element
// in EVERY position — the top-level `{z: f64[]|null}[]` param/local and the `type E =
// {z: f64[]|null}` declared spellings all loud-reject ("only … struct/union element
// arrays are supported"). Its ref-list element slot never interns, so `pushFieldStorage`
// records this loud error at the type section. Before the guards this NESTED-in-a-struct
// spelling instead CRASHED THE COMPILER twice: (1) `emitObj` read `rlElemKindTbl` out of
// bounds emitting the `{a: []}` literal (emitFail records but does not halt), and (2) with
// the outer `| string | {q: i64}` union, `structIndexOfTypeName`'s scan read the
// half-registered inline shape's `sFieldElemName` rows out of bounds during
// `internInlineShape`'s field loop. Both are now bounds-guarded (the "fbValtype"
// discipline) so the family fails LOUDLY, never traps the compiler. fuzz sweep zq0NPY
// multiobs, seed 24438928 (`{a: {a: {f: boolean} | null, f: {[string]: {[string]: i64}},
// z: f64[] | null}[], f: {f: i64}, z: {f: boolean}} | string | {q: i64}`).
function useIt(p: {a: {z: f64[] | null}[]}) { print(0) }
function go() { useIt({ a: [] }) }
go()
